      "writtenOn": "2026-07-01T05:29:47Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think throwing is the better approach,\n1. Makes the impossible visible — logged in the catch block of caller processFruCollection with the chassis path for diagnostics.\n2. Keeps normal and error semantics distinct — an empty return from getNextFruPath should mean \"iterator exhausted\", not \"something went wrong\".\n\nThe subsequent commit, m_frusCount cleanup will takes place for any pending FRUs for the chassis whose VPD collection is not triggered from the caller processFruCollection API.",
